vulnerability.name: USN-7443-3
vulnerability.description: USN-7443-1 fixed a vulnerability in Erlang. This update provides the corresponding update for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   Fabian Bäumer, Marcel Maehren, Marcus Brinkmann, and Jörg Schwenk  discovered that Erlang OTP’s SSH module incorrect handled authentication. A  remote attacker could use this issue to execute arbitrary commands without  authentication, possibly leading to a system compromise.

statements.status_notes: Erlang could be made to run programs if it received specially crafted network traffic. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
